A health worker prepares to conduct a COVID-19 coronavirus molecular test in Parkview, Johannesburg. Luca Sola / AFP JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize says he is concerned about the rise in new COVID-19 infections. The country recorded over 3,000 new coronavirus cases on Friday. Most of those infections are in the Eastern Cape. Mkhize says they have identified hotspots in that province. READ: SA records 2,514 new COVID-19 cases The cumulative total of COVD-19 infections in South Africa is 762,763. The health department also confirmed 88 new COVID-19 deaths. This brings the total to 20,759 deaths. South Africa's recoveries now stand at 707,040 which translates to a recovery rate of 92,7-percent.